					<h2><a href="https://sunshack.wordpress.com/2017/07/11/spring-slide/" rel="bookmark">Spring Slide</a></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="post-2675 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blogroll tag-alagna tag-champoluc tag-gressoney tag-italy tag-monterosa tag-off-piste tag-ski tag-skiing tag-snow tag-snowy-days">
					<div class="entry">
					<div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_2703" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2703" class="size-medium wp-image-2703" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040317.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040317.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040317.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040317.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p id="caption-attachment-2703" class="wp-caption-text">Gressoney La Trinite</p></div>
<p style="text-align:center;">For some strange reason I prepared this entry and failed to post it. Oh well, here is some snow to make you think of winter.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;">The end of my ski season. It&#8217;s always warm, snowy and a little sad as another winter on snow comes to a close. My destination was the Hamlet sized village of Gressoney La Tinite in the Monterosa ski area, in Aosta, Italy. Though I was definitely in Italy, I kept seeing German words throughout the village, and learned that the inhabitants of the villages were Walser&#8217;s who originally came from Swiss Valais. I had already spent a couple of days here a few years back, and knew I wanted to see more of the skiing. I stayed in a smart Hotel, but unfortunately my room overlooked the Kitchen dustbins, and I was treated to a nightly cacophony of empty Wine bottles being thrown into skips and the staff enjoying their Cigarette breaks directly below my room.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"> The skiing is varied and extensive. Access from Gressoney La Trinite is via a rather old 2 person chairlift. Once up on the hill the terrain opens up, and the views are great.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2711" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040324.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040324.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040324.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040324.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">Mother Nature delivered me some powder to play in. How could I resist. This is on the Alagna side of the system.</p>
<div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_2713" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2713" class="size-medium wp-image-2713" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040320.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040320.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040320.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/p1040320.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p id="caption-attachment-2713" class="wp-caption-text">Powder 100% legal!</p></div>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2716" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040349.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040349.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040349.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040349.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">Some lovely long runs above Gressoney</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2717" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040354.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040354.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040354.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040354.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2718" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040366.jpg?w=225&#038;h=300" alt="" width="225" height="300" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040366.jpg?w=225&amp;h=300 225w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040366.jpg?w=450&amp;h=600 450w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040366.jpg?w=113&amp;h=150 113w" sizes="(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">I went for a Coffee at this Mountain Hut. Thought I&#8217;d check my emails, while I was there. Price for that is 5 Euros. Be warned.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;">The home run, after a few days of warm weather. Still open, and just about skiable,</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2719" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040371.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040371.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040371.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/07/p1040371.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">I do wish that smart Hotels, would be more smart about their Bar billing. It&#8217;s not smart to try to rip of customers. Each evening I had the same drink with Dinner. Came to pay my Bill and I seem to have had a little binge. Still, a photo of each evening&#8217;s Main Course with the Bottle soon resolved the problem.</p>
					</div>
