			<div class="postwrapper wideposts" id="post-2577">
				<div class="title">
					<small>Posted by: <strong>sunshack</strong> | February 24, 2017 </small>
					<h2><a href="https://sunshack.wordpress.com/2017/02/24/contrasts-2/" rel="bookmark">Contrasts</a></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="post-2577 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-blogroll tag-brevent tag-cervinia tag-chamonix tag-france tag-italy tag-le-tour tag-les-houches tag-powder tag-ski tag-skiing tag-snow tag-switzerland tag-valais tag-vallorcine tag-zermatt">
					<div class="entry">
					<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2594" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040135.jpg?w=225&#038;h=300" alt="Matterhorn" width="225" height="300" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040135.jpg?w=225&amp;h=300 225w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040135.jpg?w=450&amp;h=600 450w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040135.jpg?w=113&amp;h=150 113w" sizes="(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">In December and January I skied 3 ski areas in 3 Countries. The conditions I experienced varied greatly. In December, I stayed in Zermatt, where conditions on the slopes had been augmented by artificial snow. Zermatt managed to open a couple of pistes back to the village. Hopping over the border into Italy at Cervinia during the same week, and I experienced the magical Powder. Of course, weather patterns play a big part of determining which resort gets the &#8220;freshies&#8221; and it was the turn of Cervinia, which shares glacier access with Zermatt.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;">I was happy that my favourite Black piste on the Zermatt side, was opened up. It was quiet, so I got stuck in straight away.</p>
<div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_2597" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2597" class="size-medium wp-image-2597" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040114.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="Furg to Furi piste" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040114.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040114.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040114.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p id="caption-attachment-2597" class="wp-caption-text">Furg to Furi piste</p></div>
<p style="text-align:center;">Ventured over to Cervinia several times. It can take quite a while to get there using the lift system. Going up onto the glacier, then skiing across the border into Italy. It was however, worth the trek.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2599" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040133.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="p1040133" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040133.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040133.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040133.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2601" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040140.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="p1040140" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040140.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040140.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040140.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"> Christmas came and went, and I made the trip out to Chamonix in January. I had snowfall for my drive out, which made for a longer trip. The upside of all that big weather was powder for my first few days. Bliss!</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2604" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040160.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="p1040160" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040160.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040160.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040160.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_2606" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2606" class="size-medium wp-image-2606" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040161.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="It's a Powder Day!" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040161.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040161.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040161.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p id="caption-attachment-2606" class="wp-caption-text">It&#8217;s a Powder Day!</p></div>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2608" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040165.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="p1040165" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040165.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040165.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040165.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">I visited Le Tour Vallorcine, expecting to find a little more of the nice soft powder. I&#8217;d not checked the wind forecast the day before I went up there. Oh dear! The off piste was hard, wind scoured crust within the system.</p>
<div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_2610" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2610" class="size-medium wp-image-2610" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040168.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="It's still snow, but not much fun" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040168.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040168.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040168.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p id="caption-attachment-2610" class="wp-caption-text">It&#8217;s still snow, but not much fun</p></div>
<p style="text-align:center;">The weather warmed up, and I thought I&#8217;d try another day at Les Houches. Some of the open pistes had insufficient snow.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2612" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040184.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="p1040184" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040184.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040184.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040184.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">Interesting snow crystals in Vallorcine.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2614" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040190.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="p1040190" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040190.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040190.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040190.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">The Bears have the right idea!</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2615" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040188.jpg?w=225&#038;h=300" alt="p1040188" width="225" height="300" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040188.jpg?w=225&amp;h=300 225w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040188.jpg?w=450&amp;h=600 450w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040188.jpg?w=113&amp;h=150 113w" sizes="(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">I rented an apartment near Brevent, which had superb views.</p>
<div data-shortcode="caption" id="attachment_2617" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2617" class="size-medium wp-image-2617" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040169.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="Room with a View!" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040169.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040169.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2017/02/p1040169.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p id="caption-attachment-2617" class="wp-caption-text">Room with a View!</p></div>
<p style="text-align:center;">So far this winter, many mainstream European resorts have been short of snowfall. I&#8217;m hoping that the latter part of the season will see bumper snow.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="postinfo">
