			<div class="postwrapper wideposts" id="post-1607">
				<div class="title">
					<small>Posted by: <strong>sunshack</strong> | November 18, 2016 </small>
					<h2><a href="https://sunshack.wordpress.com/2016/11/18/getting-high/" rel="bookmark">Getting High</a></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="post-1607 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blogroll tag-ski tag-skiing tag-switzerland tag-valais tag-zermatt">
					<div class="entry">
					<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2580" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040042.jpg?w=225&#038;h=300" alt="p1040042" width="225" height="300" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040042.jpg?w=225&amp;h=300 225w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040042.jpg?w=450&amp;h=600 450w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040042.jpg?w=113&amp;h=150 113w" sizes="(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;">I will use any excuse to get some time on skis. New Ski Boots to run in? That will do nicely. So I packed a bag and headed for some early season sliding in Zermatt. At this time of the year, it&#8217;s mostly on the Glacier, which is quite extensive, though there are not many holiday tourists, it&#8217;s mostly National Ski Teams and their Trainers. It was fun being the worst skier on the hill. The snow was in superb condition, and the weather stayed cold. It&#8217;s always a little strange to come down to a mountain village, and find that it&#8217;s really warm, and I&#8217;m way overdressed!  The Lift Company had decided that they would service the main Gondola, that week, and everyone was trying to squeeze into the old Cable Car. Long queues, it was grim!</p>
<p style="text-align:center;">Up on the Glacier, conditions were superb. Wonderful squeaky snow.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2582" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1030979.jpg?w=225&#038;h=300" alt="p1030979" width="225" height="300" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1030979.jpg?w=225&amp;h=300 225w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1030979.jpg?w=450&amp;h=600 450w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1030979.jpg?w=113&amp;h=150 113w" sizes="(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"> Great to watch, but I have no wish to try this!</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2583" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040009.jpg?w=300&#038;h=225" alt="p1040009" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040009.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040009.jpg?w=600&amp;h=450 600w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040009.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">I went for a Coffee in Italy!</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2587" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040037.jpg?w=225&#038;h=300" alt="p1040037" width="225" height="300" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040037.jpg?w=225&amp;h=300 225w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040037.jpg?w=450&amp;h=600 450w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040037.jpg?w=113&amp;h=150 113w" sizes="(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">The slopes close early in the Summer and Autumn,  so one afternoon, I went for a walk around in the old village of Zermatt. It&#8217;s very pretty, and has much more charm than the new Hotels.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2588" src="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040044.jpg?w=225&#038;h=300" alt="p1040044" width="225" height="300" srcset="https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040044.jpg?w=225&amp;h=300 225w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040044.jpg?w=450&amp;h=600 450w, https://sunshack.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/p1040044.jpg?w=113&amp;h=150 113w" sizes="(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px" /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">With access by Train from Geneva or Zurich, Zermatt is a good choice for a short ski break.</p>
